data.text:
Career Highlights

• A-10 All-Championship Team (2023)

2023: Appeared in 39 games, starting 34 • Played multiple positions, including left field, second base and shortstop • Earned a spot on the A-10 All-Championship Team after hitting .636 (7-for-11) and posting a 1.532 OPS in the event • Hit .298 with a .942 OPS, 11 doubles, one triple, five home runs and 28 RBIs • Went 3-for-5 with a double, a home run, four runs scored and five RBIs against Fordham (4/1) • Had four hits against Dayton (5/25) • Had a 14-game hit streak, second-best on the team • Reached base in 17 straight games.

2022: Played in 48 games, starting 46 at second base • Hit .201 with six doubles, two triples, two home runs and 24 RBIs • Led the team with 10 sacrifices • Had seven multi-hit games, including a high of three against William & Mary (3/15) • Drove in a high of three runs against George Mason (5/21) • Hit his first career home run at Saint Louis (5/1), then homered in the next game against Winthrop (5/4) • Reached base in 12 straight games.

2021: Played in 18 games, starting 15 as a regular late-season contributor • Hit .204 with five doubles and six RBIs • Got his first college hit on a single at Richmond (5/2), on a day when he also scored three runs and drove in two on a second single • Cleared the bases with a 3-RBI double against Saint Louis (5/20).

Before Davidson: Played at Knoxville West High, where he also played basketball • Hit .583 with a .600 on-base percentage as a senior after hitting .461 with an .533 OBP as a junior • Set the program record with 18 doubles.

Personal: Son of Brian and Martha • Born Aug. 29, 2001 • Has a sister, Katie.
